[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man arrested in Cardiff Bay flat murder investigation

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been arrested on suspicion of murder after a woman was found dead in a flat in Cardiff Bay.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Christine James, 65, was found dead by police on Wednesday, 2 March, after relatives became concerned about her whereabouts.
The man, 36, is currently in custody at Cardiff Bay Police Station.
South Wales Police has referred the matter voluntarily to the Independent Police Complaints Commission.
A 66-year-old man who was arrested on Wednesday has been released on police bail.
